Make a Jason file.

$ npm init 

Add Dependiencies in package.json file
$ npm install --save-dev [package you want to install]

This will update our package.json file devDependencies
$ npm install --save-dev gulp
$ npm install --save-dev gulp-util
$ npm install --save-dev gulp-concat
$ npm install --save-dev gulp-browserify
$ npm install --save-dev gulp-connect

Create a gulpfile.js in root to tell gulp what to do when it runs
Use nodeJS require command to pull in library.

var gulp = require('gulp');

gulp.task('log',function() {
	
});

Sass is installed with Compass, needs ruby to run, update ruby
$ sudo gem update --system
$ sudo gem install compass



